        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): load bootstrap files from agentDir alongside workspace",
        "body": "## Problem\n`src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir` only and does not read explicitly configured `agentDir`. When users configure an `agentDir` for their agents, bootstrap files placed there are ignored.\n\nFixes #29387\n\n## Fix\nModify `loadBootstrapFiles()` to also load explicitly configured `agentDir` bootstrap files, with `agentDir` files overriding same-named workspace files for correct precedence.\n\n## Test plan\n1. Verify agentDir bootstrap files are loaded alongside workspace files\n2. Verify agentDir files override same-named workspace files\n3. Run bootstrap-files test suite\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Before (broken)\n- `loadBootstrapFiles()` only reads from `workspaceDir`\n- Bootstrap files placed in configured `agentDir` are silently ignored\n- Users who set `agentDir` in agent config get no bootstrap files loaded from that directory\n\n### After (fixed)\n- `loadBootstrapFiles()` reads from both `workspaceDir` and `agentDir`\n- `agentDir` files take precedence over same-named workspace files (agentDir wins on conflict)\n- No config change needed — existing `agentDir` configs immediately pick up bootstrap files\n\n### Reproduction\n1. Configure an agent with `agentDir: \"/path/to/agent\"`\n2. Place a bootstrap file (e.g., `instructions.md`) in `/path/to/agent`\n3. Before fix: bootstrap file is not loaded; after fix: file is loaded and used\n4. Place same-named file in workspaceDir — agentDir version takes precedence\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts (37 tests, 100% pass)\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  37 passed (37)\n   Duration  2.34s\n```\n\nAll 37 bootstrap-files tests pass, covering workspace bootstrap loading, agentDir precedence, same-name override behavior, and edge cases.",
